s a dynamic concept, in particular how it has recently become more widely used and understood throughout the world. The volume introduces core concepts and delves more deeply into current trends in gastronomy, the forces which shape them and their implications for tourism. The book is multidisciplinary and will appeal to researchers in the fields of gastronomy, hospitality, tourism and media studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jul 2020) 0aFood in popular culture. 0aFood tourism. 0aMass mediaxSocial aspects. 4aCuisine. 4aDestinations. 4aFood. 4aGastronomy. 4aHospitality. 4aMedia. 4aSocial media. 4aTourism marketing. 4aTourism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh1 aBest, Gary, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLade, Clare, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLaing, Jennifer, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStrickland, Paul, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184541575440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845415754423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781845415754.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK